# Ecommerce Consumer Behavior Analysis – 2025

📊 Tool Used: Excel  
📁 Deliverables: KPI Dashboard, Final Business Report

## 🔍 Project Overview
This project analyzes consumer behavior data from a 2025 ecommerce dataset to uncover purchasing patterns, churn risks, and satisfaction trends. The goal was to produce actionable insights for strategic decision-making.

## 🎯 Objectives
- Identify churn risk factors
- Understand discount sensitivity
- Segment customers by behavior and satisfaction
- Visualize key KPIs through a dashboard

## 📌 Key Insights
- Churn Risk: 26% overall, with Books & Office Supplies highest
- Customer Satisfaction: Avg = 5/10
- High Return Rates linked to low satisfaction
- Discount Sensitivity: 52% use discounts; these customers spend less on average

## 📈 Dashboard Features
- Churn Risk by Category
- Return Rate by Product Category
- Average Order Value (AOV)
- Discount Sensitivity Impact
- Customer Satisfaction by Channel

📎 See: [`Ecommerce_Dashboard_2025.xlsx`](./Ecommerce_Dashboard_2025.xlsx)

## 📚 Methods
- Data cleaning & wrangling in Excel
- KPI creation with formulas & pivot tables
- Data visualization with pivot charts and conditional formatting
- Business reporting structured in 4 project phases

## 🧠 What I Learned
- How to calculate customer churn indicators
- Effective use of Excel for segmentation & what-if analysis
- Visual storytelling with dashboards

